  "faqQ1": "How much commission does Rurboo charge?",
  "faqA1": "Rurboo charges a standard commission of 20% on the total fare for each completed ride. This helps us maintain the platform, market to riders, and provide support to you.",
  "faqQ2": "How do I get paid?",
  "faqA2": "Your earnings (minus the 20% commission) are accumulated in your driver wallet. Payouts are processed weekly to your registered bank account or UPI ID.",
  "faqQ3": "What if a rider cancels?",
  "faqA3": "If a rider cancels after you have already traveled a significant distance towards the pickup location, you may be eligible for a cancellation fee.",
  "faqQ4": "How can I improve my rating?",
  "faqA4": "Keep your vehicle clean, be polite to riders, drive safely, and follow the navigation route. Good service leads to higher ratings.",
  "faqQ5": "Is there a penalty for declining rides?",
  "faqA5": "We understand you may not accept every ride. However, a high acceptance rate may unlock special incentives.",
  "faqQ6": "How do I contact support?",
  "faqA6": "You can contact support via the 'Help & Support' section in the app. Email: adarshpandey@rurboo.com or Phone: +91 8810220691",

